data.title: Teamsters at Zenith Logistics in Cincinnati ratify new contract, including pay increase and improved benefits.
data.description: Workers belonging to Local Union 100 have secured a significant pay raise, comprehensive health benefits through Teamsters, and better working conditions. The members, employed at Zenith Logistics which serves Kroger, approved a new collective bargaining agreement for six years.

data.title: SPX FLOW offers support for customers with new maintenance, spares, and service agreements for 2026. #manufacturing #SPXFLOW
data.description: In Charlotte, North Carolina on October 30, 2025, SPX FLOW is aiding customers worldwide in gearing up for 2026 by offering innovative proactive maintenance, quick-ship spare parts, and customized service contracts to ensure optimal performance of essential equipment. As the year 2025 comes to a close, manufacturers and producers are benefiting from these initiatives.

data.title: Black-Owned The Old G gin wins "Best Gin in Show" at Global Spirit Awards. Introduces new 200ml bottle. Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: Following the recent release of a 200ml pocket bottle, The Old G, a London Dry gin brand that is Black- and minority-owned, has received an award in Las Vegas on October 30, 2025. This recognition comes at a time when the brand is expanding its cultural impact and experiencing rapid growth, even in the face of industry challenges.

data.title: FXCubic's FXCubic Bridge processed record 3,000 yards in trading volume in Sep 2025, Company milestone reached.
data.description: In London on October 30, 2025, FXCubic, a top player in liquidity aggregation and risk management technology, revealed that its primary product, the FXCubic Bridge, handled more than 3,000 yards in trading volume in September 2025. This achievement represents a significant milestone for the company.

data.title: Recreatives Industries (OTC: RECX) halves authorized shares from 1.45B to 700M to boost shareholder value.
data.description: Recreatives Industries (OTC: RECX) has reduced its authorized shares from 1.45 billion to 700 million. This move is aimed at strengthening disciplined equity management and enhancing shareholder value.

data.title: VinFast's VF 8 bridges Vietnam and Canada's EV differences. 100k+ vehicles delivered in Vietnam.
data.description: VinFast's VF 8 model is symbolizing the connection between different approaches to electrification as Vietnam rapidly progresses and Canada steadily shifts in that direction. This electric vehicle is showcasing the boldness of a new player in the market alongside the cautiousness of a nation adapting to electric transportation. While global interest in electric vehicles has been varied, with some markets experiencing a decline, Vietnam is experiencing an increase. VinFast, Vietnam's domestic automaker, has successfully distributed over 100,000 vehicles.

data.title: MeaningSphere launches new digital learning experiences for U.S. workers to find more fulfilling work. Media release on Oct. 30, 2025.

data.title: DICK'S Sporting Goods Foundation donates $2M to The Josh Gibson Foundation for new youth sports facility in PA.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, a collaboration between The DICK'S Sporting Goods Foundation and The Josh Gibson Foundation was revealed. The partnership introduces the establishment of the Josh Gibson Champions Club & Sports Matter Center. This initiative signifies a significant development in youth sports support, emphasizing a focus on nurturing the athletic potential of the younger generation. The center's name reflects the merging of the notable figures: Josh Gibson and Sports Matter. This joint venture seeks to invigorate the landscape of youth sports, underscoring the importance of investing in the upcoming sporting talents.

data.title: Inventor from Texas creates RANGEL SHALLOW SOCKET RATCHET to combine ratchet and socket. Simplifies nut turning process.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, an inventor from Baytown, Texas shared their innovative creation: the RANGEL SHALLOW SOCKET RATCHET. The inventor believed that merging a ratchet and socket into a single tool would enhance efficiency. This new invention aims to streamline the task of turning nuts and bolts.

data.title: La La Land coffee chain Receives Investment from Stripes to Expand Nationally in the U.S. - PRNewswire, Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: La popular marca La La Land ha anunciado una asociación con Stripes para impulsar su crecimiento en todo Estados Unidos. Con esta inversión estratégica, La La Land busca acelerar su expansión a nivel nacional. La empresa, conocida por revolucionar el concepto de cafetería con su distintivo menú y marca icónica, está posicionada para un crecimiento significativo en el mercado. La asociación con Stripes representa un paso clave en la estrategia de crecimiento de La La Land, brindándole la oportunidad de fortalecer su presencia a través de una importante inversión.

data.title: International Paper Co. reported a third-quarter loss of 43 cents per share, missing analyst expectations. Revenue was $6.22 billion, down from estimates of $6.50 billion. CEO highlights resilience.
data.description: International Paper Co. (NYSE: IP) saw a decline in its stock value following the release of its third-quarter earnings report. The company announced an adjusted loss of 43 cents per share for the quarter, contrasting sharply with the 33 cents per share earnings reported in the same period last year. Analysts had anticipated a profit of 47 cents per share, leading to this disappointing result. Despite revenues increasing by 56% from $3.98 billion in the previous year's quarter to $6.22 billion, it still fell short of the $6.50 billion consensus estimate. The adjusted EBITDA for the third quarter in 2025 stood at $1.01 billion, with $153 million coming from the Global Cellulose Fibres segment, now classified as a discontinued operation.

data.title: XRP drops 6% in 24 hours as it slips below key support levels. XRP is currently priced at $2.46 with a market cap of $148.2 billion. EthNasyonal believes this could be a setup for an upcoming breakout.
data.description: XRP has recently fallen below important support levels despite the strong fundamentals in its ecosystem. The crypto's current price stands at $2.46, with a market cap of $148.2 billion and a 7-day trend showing a 2.8% increase. In comparison, Bitcoin is priced at $107,954.65 with a market cap of $2.15 trillion, experiencing a 1.2% decrease, while Ethereum is priced at $3,803.93 with a market cap of $458.8 billion, also down 1.2%. Traders are interpreting this movement as a potential setup for an imminent breakout. Notably, EtherNasyonal highlighted that XRP has been testing resistance levels consistently and accumulating above support, suggesting the asset is gearing up for a breakout. With each resistance test, sellers appear to be weakening as buyers absorb the supply and gain momentum, setting the stage for a potential bullish move.
